[thinking] 
[thinking] I see that I need to figure out the service lookup test. Maybe I can set the Thread Context ClassLoader (TCCL) with a ClassLoader that has no service resources. By creating a custom ClassLoader, I could override the getResources method. When the classLoader is null, the system ClassLoader will find the service instead, which makes me wonder how to properly handle this for properties constructors. I might need to update the test to reflect assertions for the default constructor effectively.
